ers of the name was Robert le Grosvenor of Budworth, who was granted lands by the Earl of Chester in 1160. The family's fortunes were founded by Thomas Grosvenor (born 1656), who in 1677 married an heiress, Mary Davies, whose inheritance included Ebury Farm, Middlesex. This now forms an area of central London that includes Grosvenor Square and Belgrave Square."],"variants":[{"name":"Gravenor","meanings":["English (of Norman origin): nickname from Old French <i>grand</i> ‘big, tall’ + <i>veneor</i> ‘hunter’. Compare   Grosvenor  ."]}]},{"name":"Katherine","type":"FIRST","meanings":["Greek: Same as Catherine."],"variants":[]}],"lifeSummary":"Katherine Grosvenor was born about 1267, in Little Budworth, Cheshire, England, United Kingdom as the daughter of Robert Grosvenor and Margaret Wastneys. She married William de Venables before 1289. They were the parents of at least 3 daughters."},"et":{"abt 1267–":"umbes 1267–Surnud","1245–Female":"1245–Surnud","1267–Female":"1267–Surnud","1324–Female":"1324–Surnud","1276–1345":"1276–1345","1289–Female":"1289–Surnud","1291–Female":"1291–Surnud","1320–1386":"1320–1386","–Male":"Surnud","–Female":"Surnud","before 1289":"enne 1289","before 1245":"enne 1245","abt 1291":"umbes 1291","1291":"1291","abt 1267":"umbes 1267","abt 1289":"umbes 1289","1324":"1324","1345":"1345","1289":"1289","1267":"1267","1245":"1245","1320":"1320","1386":"1386","1276":"1276","of Little Budworth, Chshr, Engl":"Little Budworth, Cheshire, Inglismaa, United Kingdom","of Bradwell, Chshr, Engl":"Cheshire, Inglismaa, United Kingdom","Europe":"Europe","Kinderton, Cheshire, England":"Kinderton, Cheshire, Inglismaa, United Kingdom"},"fi":{"abt 1267–":"noin 1267–Kuollut","1245–Female":"1245–Kuollut","1267–Female":"1267–Kuollut","1324–Female":"1324–Kuollut","1276–1345":"1276–1345","1289–Female":"1289–Kuollut","1291–Female":"1291–Kuollut","1320–1386":"1320–1386","–Male":"Kuollut","–Female":"Kuollut","before 1289":"ennen vuotta 1289","before 1245":"ennen vuotta 1245","a